The Rev. Al Sharpton continued to protest the decision to transfer the trial of the four white police officers accused of shooting Amadou Diallo to Albany, and Winnie Madikizela-Mandela appeared with him Saturday and condemned police brutality.
Jury selection is scheduled to begin Jan. 31 in the trial of the four police officers charged with killing Amadou Diallo, an unarmed West African immigrant.
The trial was moved to Albany after defense attorneys argued that the officers could not get a fair trial in the Bronx.
